search_query: Museum of the Shenandoah Valley Winchester museum
extract: The Museum of the Shenandoah Valley (MSV) is a museum complex located in Winchester, Virginia, that opened in 2005. The institution comprises the museum building designed by architect Michael Graves, the historic Glen Burnie House, and a surrounding landscape of formal gardens. The museum focuses on the art, history, and material culture of the Shenandoah Valley and its surrounding region.
